message: “Iowa is not immune from human trafficking,” Reynolds said in the release. “I know [the project] will support the good work we’re already doing, from the strong laws we have on the books to the Office to Combat Human Trafficking we established in the Department of Public Safety to our law-enforcement officers participating in training programs.”

data.description: Iowa Gov. Kim Reynolds’ new statewide initiative trains hotel and motel employees on how to stop human trafficking. By Molly Hunter molly-hunter@uiowa.edu The Iowa Network Against Human Trafficking…
data.title: Hotel staff train against trafficking
